fr.sii.ogham.sms.builder.cloudhopper

Class DefaultConnectRetryablePredicate

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.sms.builder.cloudhopper.DefaultConnectRetryablePredicate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Predicate<Throwable>

    public class DefaultConnectRetryablePredicate
extends Object
implements Predicate<Throwable>
    Default predicate used to indicate if the error raised by Cloudhopper is fatal or not. It returns true if the error is not fatal (means that a new retry can be attempted). It returns false if the error is fatal and no retry must be attempted.

    Here is the list of cases where there should have no retries:

    • There is a fatal JVM Error (like OutOfMemoryError for example).
    • A bind request has been sent to the SMSC and it has responded with an error indicating that the credentials are invalid
    • A bind request has been sent to the SMSC and it has responded with an error indicating that the system_type is invalid
    • A bind request has been sent to the SMSC and it has responded with an error indicating that client is already bound

      • fatalJvmError

        public boolean fatalJvmError(Throwable error)
        Checks whether the error has been raised due to a Java Error. Errors should not be ignored. For example, if there is a OutOfMemoryError, retrying may result in consuming more memory and totally crash the JVM or hang the system.
        Parameters:
        error - the raised error
        Returns:
        true if the error is fatal JVM error

      • invalidCredentials

        public boolean invalidCredentials(Throwable error)
        Checks whether the error has been raised because the SMSC has sent a response to a bind request indicating that the credentials are invalid (wrong system_id or password).

        If the credentials are invalid, there is no point in retrying to connect.

        Parameters:
        error - the raised error
        Returns:
        true if the error is issued due to a bind failure (wrong credentials)
